Description: I am still trying to thin out my herd of stringed instruments. It’s getting harder and harder since I am attached to all of them at this point. This listing is a Frankenstein…Warmoth (I was told swamp ash) body and birdseye maple neck. DiMarzio single coil pups; DiMarzio area 58(2) and 61 stacked, plus a piezo in the bridge with stereo output and a blend control. The top knob is a single volume for the 3 single coil DiMarzios then a tone for the same. The third knob controls the volume of the piezo. The output jack is tip-ring-sleeve. A normal guitar cord won’t play the piezo, though you can back it out one “click” to activate the piezo and bypass the single coils. To have them all on a stereo jack would have to be split into two and bi-amped or fed into 2 channels on a board or preamp. Custom sparkle blue paint top with a gold stripe separating the natural gloss back. Sperzel matte finish locking tuners ($65). Professionally built and finished. Frets were leveled with Plek machine and polished. L.R.Baggs Vintage Tremolo Piezo X-Bridge ($169) gives an acoustic style sound. It will ship with the whammy bar but this guitar was set up with a bottomed out bridge. Gig bag included. It will ship in the bag, then bubble wrapped and boxed. I will be listing about 20 guitars and basses, guitar parts and microphones in the next few months. I ship fast and currently own a 100% feedback rating as a buyer and seller on EBay (860+ transactions, a member since 2001).
Title: Warmoth Staratocaster Fender Licensed Guitar Custom 4 pickups DiMarzio
